---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy • Secura Security Suite">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[#050507] text-neutral-200 selection:bg-cyan-500 selection:text-black flex flex-col justify-between">
    <Header />

    <div class="flex-1 relative">
      <!-- Grid Background overlay -->
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(rgba(6,182,212,0.03)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(6,182,212,0.03)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:32px_32px] opacity-40 pointer-events-none"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/3 w-[450px] h-[450px] bg-cyan-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>

      <!-- Content Container -->
      <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 z-10">
        
        <!-- Header back button -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <a 
            href="/" 
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-mono text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors uppercase tracking-wider group"
          >
            <span class="transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform inline-block">&larr;</span>
            <span>Back to Home</span>
          </a>
        </div>

      <!-- Hero Header -->
      <div class="border-b border-neutral-900 pb-10 mb-12">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-cyan-950/40 border border-cyan-500/30 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan-400 mb-6 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(6,182,212,0.1)]">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-cyan-400"></span>
          <span>SECURA COMPLIANCE INFRASTRUCTURE</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-white mb-6 font-mono">
          PRIVACY POLICY
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-neutral-500">
          Last Updated: July 17, 2026 &bull; Version 2.0.1 (Stable)
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Policy Clauses -->
      <div class="space-y-10 text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed font-sans max-w-3xl">
        
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">1. Absolute Zero-Knowledge Architectural Mandate</h2>
          <p>
            Secura operates under a strict, mathematically-provable <strong>Zero-Knowledge Policy</strong>. The application uses client-side Web Cryptography APIs (AES-GCM encryption with 256-bit keys) to encrypt your critical credentials, notes, and budgets inside your web browser prior to storage.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-cyan-400 font-mono text-xs">
            Result: We have zero access, visibility, or mechanisms to reconstruct your master decryption password. If you lose your master password, Secura cannot recover your encrypted records.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">2. Data We Gather & Store</h2>
          <p>
            To facilitate secure synchronization across your devices, we store:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1.5 mt-3 text-neutral-300 pl-2">
            <li><strong>Encrypted Payload Records:</strong> Secure password entries, generated client invoices, and logged transactions, formatted as ciphertexts.</li>
            <li><strong>Authentication Metadata:</strong> Hashed credentials via Firebase Authentication services to secure user access boundaries.</li>
            <li><strong>Client Settings:</strong> High-level locale preferences, display language configurations, and interface themes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">3. No Advertising & Sell-Thru Protection</h2>
          <p>
            Secura does not partner with behavioral advertisement brokers or utilize tracking pixels. Your operational logs, budgets, and billing profiles are strictly confidential. We do not sell, license, or lease corporate telemetry records or contact information to any third parties.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">4. Security Infrastructure Logs & Backups</h2>
          <p>
            Our host environments log basic TCP/IP metadata and authorization event headers solely for firewalls, load balancing, and preventing distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) requests. These firewall traces are purged automatically on a rolling 14-day sequence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-md font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">5. User Sovereign Rights (GDPR & CCPA Compliant)</h2>
          <p>
            Because we do not keep decrypted archives of your records, your right to erase, audit, or restrict processing is entirely under your control. You may permanently delete your account, credentials, and data logs directly within the Secura Dashboard settings menu at any time.
          </p>
        </div>

       </div>

      <!-- Footer stamp -->
      <div class="border-t border-neutral-900 mt-16 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-neutral-600">SECURA PRIVACY OFFICERS REGISTRY &bull; EU-GDPR SECURE</span>
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-neutral-500">SHA-256 HASH: 92F05D...E31B</span>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</div>
</Layout>
